txt.en: The leaders of the Mordor Orcs at Nîn-stazg are amongst the most terrifying foes ever beheld by the Rohirrim of Floodwend.

'I am worried about the leaders of this new Orc encampment, my friend. Will you defeat the overseers of this rabble? The siege-machines being assembled down there look to be a most threatening force for Floodwend.'
Nîn-stazg can be found south-east of Floodwend, just out of sight of the town's walls.\n\nYou should defeat Mordor Orc-overseers at Nîn-stazg.

'You were very brave to defeat the leaders of Nîn-stazg, [placeholder]. Floodwend would not have survived the assault they led, especially with those siege-weapons under their sway.\n\n'Not many warriors could have done as you did. I am very pleased to have you on our side.'
Thane Radwig stands on a hill overlooking Nîn-stazg.\n\nYou should speak with Radwig.
'My lady Etta has sent us to protect the Thane. He should not go into battle, but he may observe the battle from here, should he wish it.'
'My lady Etta has sent us to protect the Thane. He should not go into battle, but he may observe the battle from here, should he wish it.'
'The Overseers are down below in Nîn-stazg, [placeholder]. I fear they are too strong a match for my sword.'
Return to Radwig outside of Nîn-stazg
